The paper discusses collaboration in the context of information seeking, which is a core topic in information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also discusses the concept of collaboration and proposes a model for Collaborative Information Seeking (CIS), which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper touches on issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social informatics (cs.SI) as they relate to collaboration and information seeking.
